# Mandatory version bump on every change

Every change in this repo MUST bump the application version. No exceptions.
This applies to features, bug fixes, deployment fixes, docs/README edits,
copy/i18n tweaks, CSS-only tweaks, and dependency bumps.

## Two locations to update (in the same commit)

1. `index.html` — the `<span id="app-footer-version">` text in the floating
   footer near the bottom of the file (currently `v1.1.1`).
2. `package.json` — the `"version"` field (currently `"1.1.1"`).

Both must show the **same** number after your change.

## Semver rules

- **patch** (`x.y.Z` → `x.y.Z+1`): fixes, docs, chores, deployment fixes,
  internal refactors with no user-visible behavior change.
- **minor** (`x.Y.0` → `x.(Y+1).0`): new user-visible feature, new UI,
  new option, new language, etc.
- **major** (`X.0.0` → `(X+1).0.0`): breaking changes (file format,
  storage key migrations without compat, removed features, etc.).

## Example

```html
<!-- index.html -->
<span id="app-footer-version" class="app-footer-version">v1.2.0</span>
```

```json
// package.json
{ "version": "1.2.0" }
```

## Checklist before committing

- [ ] Did I change anything in this repo? → Yes → bump required.
- [ ] Did I update **both** `index.html` and `package.json` to the
      **same** new version?
- [ ] Does the bump match semver (patch / minor / major)?

If you skip this, the floating footer will lie to users about what
version they're running. Don't skip it.
